post: {'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Specialists working for the government could provide the necessary education on the subject of responsible substance use. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Allowing people to become addicted merely so we can understand addiction is socially and medically irresponsible. I believe legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[In 2017](https://www.kialo.com/all-drugs-should-be-legalized-7100/7100.0=7100.1+7100.297), there were more direct deaths from alcohol consumption than from drug consumption.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Education and information might not be enough to ensure thoughtful drug use.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Since drug addicts have an impaired sense of \\(rational\\) judgement, drug addiction is detrimental to personal autonomy.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "A lack of visible violence doesn't mean that companies are not behaving in a manner which is damaging to society. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "[Ricin](https://emergency.cdc.gov/agent/ricin/facts.asp), a highly poisonous substance, is created from castor beans. That's why all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Professional addiction treatment is usually [expensive](https://www.addictioncenter.com/rehab-questions/cost-of-drug-and-alcohol-treatment/). I believe all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Many poor people use drugs as a temporary escape from poverty [\\(Scottish Drugs Forum, p. 12\\)](http://www.dldocs.stir.ac.uk/documents/drugpovertylitrev.pdf). Criminalization of this behavior does not help them.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will help contain the dangerous drug cartels. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Drug users will encourage other people, who do not know how to handle drugs and/or aren't smart and/or mature enough to try it. I believe legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'There is no guarantee that a similar compound will always exist.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Bettering education surrounding date rape and the drugs used for it would improve levels of prevention. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In the long run, the standing of the U.S. government did not suffer from ending the Alcohol Prohibition in the 1930s. Any potential reputational damage from ending marijuana or other prohibitions would be fleeting.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The only way to know if the related compound acts the same is by doing the research that was banned in the first place. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug legalization improves government finances.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "It can be argued that the terms 'recreational' and 'medicinal' are interchangeable. So all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drugs are an experience that can build character.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The US government has [previously supported](https://www.ozy.com/flashback/when-the-government-said-marijuana-made-you-crazy/88232) the claim that marijuana use causes individuals to rape and murder others, or commit suicide. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'This is a tautological argument, presupposing that prohibiting drugs is morally right.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'People would prefer less addicting drugs, so as to lessen the risk of taking them. This would lead to companies to develop less addictive drugs as well.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[The human right to personal autonomy](http://www.corteidh.or.cr/tablas/r26750.pdf) should include the freedom to take drugs.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Currently medical professionals can and do discriminate against those who use substances simply because they're illegal. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalising all drugs may give private companies incentives to advertise/promote the use of those, potentially leading to an increase the overall drug use.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The anxiety induced by the threat of arrest can be a cause for the violent paranoia episodes some users experience while under the influence emotion enhancing substances.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drugs are insanely profitable at a relatively low level of effort, as opposed to other crimes.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If legalised, drug users could be less likely to leave dangerous paraphernalia \\(broken pipes, syringes, etc.\\) behind in public places as the fear of criminal penalties for the possession of drug paraphernalia would no longer be an issue. This would lessen risk of disease and injury. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'There has been [no scientific consensus](https://newatlas.com/study-effects-ecstasy/10995/) on the long-term effects of ecstasy use.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'This is a tautological argument, presupposing that prohibiting drugs is morally right.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The correlation between drug use and crime is fuelled at least partly by prohibition.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalisation will at length normalize drug use, which can lead to excess use as with alcohol \\(drinking games, binge drinking\\) which can be far more dangerous when done with hard drugs.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Psychedelics are often used for [one-off, recreational and spiritual](https://www.livescience.com/61902-psychedelic-drugs-change-personality.html) experiences. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Some drugs are highly addictive; [addiction is defined as a disease](https://www.centeronaddiction.org/what-addiction/addiction-disease) by most medical associations.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Many currently illegal drugs make substantial positive contributions to human culture. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Fewer [productive](https://www.houstonchronicle.com/business/outside-the-boardroom/article/Mass-incarceration-hurts-U-S-economy-7434722.php) people will be in jail. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The [war on drugs](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/War_on_drugs) in the US was intended to be used as a tool to criminalise certain ethnic groups.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drug cartels will not cease their activities if drugs are legalised. They will simply move to other areas to keep their profits \\(drugs for children, black market drugs, human trafficking\\). So drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Legalising drug use would not significantly increase the consumption of drugs. That's why all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'During the prohibition of alcoholic beverages between 1920 and 1930 in the US, there were multiple negative impacts on consumers.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Cocaine](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Drug_harmfulness#/media/File:HarmCausedByDrugsTable.svg) is less harmful than alcohol, and only slightly more addictive. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In the long run, the standing of the U.S. government did not suffer from ending the Alcohol Prohibition in the 1930s. Any potential reputational damage from ending marijuana or other prohibitions would be fleeting.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Something being illegal makes the entire area "tainted." Talking about how to do something illegal is seen as encouraging said activity, and "sending the wrong signals."'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalizing drugs will help treat addicts. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'While neither seems acceptable, most would rather face prejudice than prison. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'When obtaining drugs legally people can be sure that the drugs are pure and accurately measured. With the illegal drug market drugs are often mis-sold, inaccurately measured or cut with other substances.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The government specifies what is unacceptable through prohibition. Taxation is how the government discourages. The government is only "encouraging" if they provide aid or assistance.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': '[Many drug users](https://www.drugabuse.gov/publications/drugs-brains-behavior-science-addiction/drug-misuse-addiction) do not consider the negative repercussions of drug use and are convinced they can easily control their use. So drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The first [anti-opium laws](http://www.drugpolicy.org/issues/brief-history-drug-war) in the 1870s were directed at Chinese immigrants. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Various currently illegal drugs have valuable medical properties; these substances may have the potential to solve problems in our society such as mental health issues. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug cartels destabilize Latin America. With legalization they would disappear and Latin America would gain stability.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The legalization of all drugs gives the possibility to control the age group of people participating in the drugs. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'People in poor health or overdosing on drugs are often not taken to receive medical attention for fear of criminal prosecution.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'No alcohol or tobacco company has openly killed anyone to continue selling their product.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Ketamine](https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/322534.php?iacp), a promising alternative to opioids, is currently banned. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will allow governments to fight addictive drugs more effectively. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "It is hard to determine whether the drugs actually allowed these artists to make these pieces of art or whether they just happened also to be using drugs because they had troubled minds. Sober people can be great artists. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "It's important to have a standardized quantity of an active substance of controlled quality to prevent overdosing unwanted effects. I think all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'While it might be better for society if a corporation created a less addictive drug, the actual incentive would be to create the most addictive drug imaginable. The corporation would then patent this to own a monopoly and charge a huge amount for continued use.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'A more substantial part of society will be exposed to the harmful and dangerous side effects of drugs.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalization runs the danger of increased drug use that could impair people from doing jobs safely, making work places more dangerous.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug legalization improves government finances.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The human body is very complex; a given drug can have quite subtle aspects. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "In a truly free society self regulation should be our privilege. You are free to not use drugs, and you should be just as free to use them. That's why all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Legalizing drugs does not imply you may use them on someone without their permission. It's already illegal to give someone else a narcotic they were not prescribed, even though the drug itself is legal. I think all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The illegal consumption of heroin without any satisfactory hygiene conditions [supports](https://www.drugabuse.gov/publications/research-reports/heroin/why-are-heroin-users-special-risk-contracting-hivaids-hepatitis-b-c) the development of HIV.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will help contain the dangerous drug cartels. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Addictions can lead to improper care of children, relatives, or any person \\(even animals\\) who depends on the user.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'A part of the "forbidden fruit" effect is that drugs provide short-term benefit \\(the "high"\\) in exchange for long-term cost \\(negative health impacts\\).'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will help reduce social rifts.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will lead to increased import/export options for medicines/drugs that are only available overseas and that were banned in the domestic market. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Since these would most likely be legally bought products, it would be much easier for the authorities have control over it, as opposed to illegally produced and smuggled goods.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The drug industry, like alcohol and tobacco, can be heavily taxed, generating high revenues. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
